  "prompt": "Why did Apple change its name from Apple Computers Incorporated to Apple Inc?\"?",
  "response": "Apple changed its name from Apple Computer, Inc. to Apple Inc. in January 2007. The decision was made to reflect the company's expansion beyond just computers into a broader range of consumer electronics, software, and services. With the introduction of products like the iPod, iPhone, and later the iPad, Apple was positioning itself as a leader in various technology markets, not just the personal computer sector. The name change was part of a rebranding effort to signify this evolution and to better represent the company's diverse product offerings.",
